The Reagan administration protestedfor the first time the constitutionality of the 1978 specialprosecutor law that led to a current investigation of theIran-contra scandal.    The constitutional attack by Assistant Attorney GeneralJohn Bolton was the first official public objection, althoughreportedly the administration privately has opposed the Ethicsin Government Act.    Bolton told a Senate subcommittee the administration"believes there are grave constitutional problems" with the lawthat sets up court-appointed independent prosecutors, orindependent counsels, to probe high ranking governmentofficials. Reuter&#3;